01:51:21.990 --> 01:51:25.030
My name is Irene Chen, and
I am a proud representative

01:51:25.030 --> 01:51:26.905
of Cabot House on the
senior class committee.

01:51:26.905 --> 01:51:30.210
[CHEERS]

01:51:30.210 --> 01:51:31.960
Hi, my name is
Ginny Fahs, and I am

01:51:31.960 --> 01:51:34.721
one of your 2014
senior class marshals.

01:51:34.721 --> 01:51:37.180
[CHEERS]

01:51:37.180 --> 01:51:41.110
We are very honored today to
introduce our featured guest

01:51:41.110 --> 01:51:44.740
and our keynote speaker,
Sheryl Sandberg, who

01:51:44.740 --> 01:51:47.420
has made significant
contributions in government,

01:51:47.420 --> 01:51:50.120
business, and technology.

01:51:50.120 --> 01:51:53.440
Sheryl graduated
from Harvard in 1991,

01:51:53.440 --> 01:51:56.550
a time when laptops
didn't exist and very

01:51:56.550 --> 01:51:59.510
few students used computers.

01:51:59.510 --> 01:52:01.920
Sheryl used Harvard's
computer system

01:52:01.920 --> 01:52:04.410
only once as an
undergraduate, to run

01:52:04.410 --> 01:52:07.260
regressions for
her senior thesis.

01:52:07.260 --> 01:52:12.240
She remembers storing her data
on large, heavy magnetic tapes

01:52:12.240 --> 01:52:16.440
that she had to lug in
big boxes around campus.

01:52:16.440 --> 01:52:19.110
She had to stay up all
night spinning tapes

01:52:19.110 --> 01:52:21.200
to input her thesis
data, and when

01:52:21.200 --> 01:52:23.980
she tried to execute
her final calculations,

01:52:23.980 --> 01:52:27.610
she brought down the
entire computer system.

01:52:27.610 --> 01:52:30.870
So years before Facebook's
founder Mark Zuckerberg

01:52:30.870 --> 01:52:33.600
famously crashed the
harbor computer network,

01:52:33.600 --> 01:52:36.500
our speaker beat him to it.

01:52:36.500 --> 01:52:38.850
The data was worth
the crash, and Sheryl

01:52:38.850 --> 01:52:42.980
graduated with a summa cum
laude degree in economics.

01:52:42.980 --> 01:52:44.730
She went on to Harvard
Business School

01:52:44.730 --> 01:52:48.120
where she graduated top
of her class in 1995,

01:52:48.120 --> 01:52:50.000
and later served as
the Chief of Staff

01:52:50.000 --> 01:52:53.460
to the United States Secretary
of the Treasury, Larry Summers,

01:52:53.460 --> 01:52:56.620
who had been her thesis adviser.

01:52:56.620 --> 01:53:00.220
In 2001 she joined Google
in its early stages

01:53:00.220 --> 01:53:03.890
as vice president of global
online sales and operations.

01:53:03.890 --> 01:53:07.640
Then in 2008, Mark
Zuckerberg approached her

01:53:07.640 --> 01:53:10.640
about joining a growing
company called Facebook.

01:53:10.640 --> 01:53:13.570
Sheryl became Facebook's
Chief Operating Officer

01:53:13.570 --> 01:53:15.490
and just celebrated
her sixth year there.

01:53:18.260 --> 01:53:20.470
During her undergraduate
years, Sheryl

01:53:20.470 --> 01:53:22.700
was an enthusiastic
Harvard booster

01:53:22.700 --> 01:53:25.550
who gave tours with the
Crimson Key society,

01:53:25.550 --> 01:53:28.380
taught aerobics in the
MAC five days a week,

01:53:28.380 --> 01:53:30.910
and served as a big
sister for a program

01:53:30.910 --> 01:53:34.220
through the Phillips
Brooks House Association.

01:53:34.220 --> 01:53:38.940
Today Cheryl is aiming to
be every woman's big sister.

01:53:38.940 --> 01:53:43.050
In 2013 she released
her first book, Lean In,

01:53:43.050 --> 01:53:46.700
which looks at barriers both
internal and external that

01:53:46.700 --> 01:53:48.740
prevent women from
taking leadership

01:53:48.740 --> 01:53:50.840
roles in the workplace.

01:53:50.840 --> 01:53:54.880
Her book inspired the Lean In
movement, which provides women

01:53:54.880 --> 01:53:57.250
with tools and community
support to help

01:53:57.250 --> 01:53:59.840
them achieve their ambitions.

01:53:59.840 --> 01:54:01.860
In selecting a
keynote speaker, we

01:54:01.860 --> 01:54:04.230
were hoping to find someone
who had demonstrated

01:54:04.230 --> 01:54:06.680
an extraordinary
ability to succeed,

01:54:06.680 --> 01:54:09.900
someone who has taken
significant professional risks,

01:54:09.900 --> 01:54:13.850
someone who has been an advocate
for a pressing social issue,

01:54:13.850 --> 01:54:16.680
and someone who can
lead us all in aerobics.

01:54:16.680 --> 01:54:19.010
[LAUGHTER]

01:54:19.010 --> 01:54:20.960
Sheryl meets all these criteria.

01:54:20.960 --> 01:54:22.700
Please welcome Sheryl Sandberg.

01:54:22.700 --> 01:54:26.508
[APPLAUSE]

01:54:26.508 --> 01:54:27.008
Thank you.

01:54:27.008 --> 01:54:28.000
Thank you guys.

01:54:31.472 --> 01:54:32.464
Thank you.

01:54:35.450 --> 01:54:37.710
Congratulations everyone.

01:54:37.710 --> 01:54:41.116
You made it.

